			<span class="otherdetails" id="comment_otherdetails_64499329"></span>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64499329"><p>The Technocracy movement in the early 20th century predicted the same thing. That as productivity increases, fewer and fewer people are needed to work in order to support the needs and wants of the rest of us. That automation would eventually eliminate labor. And one consequence is that the price system would also end, as personal wealth ceases to be meaningful. I don't necessarily agree with their hypothesis, but Elon Musk stumbling onto the idea like a high frat boy isn't surprising.</p></div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_64499329">

