	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64499601"><p>Could also well be the other way around. If there is no scarcity of something, there is no reason to hoard. Hoarding is, by definition, wasteful. Someone stockpiles something to ensure his access to a limited resource which depletes the resource, disallows access to that resource for others and requires them to create more of it, potentially at less favorable conditions or with more wasteful production means.</p><p>That way, a "free" resource can actually mean that, with the lack to stockpile it, the resource gets<span class="substr"> </span></p></div>
	</div>

